   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Review Sentiment Trend Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes product review text and ratings over time to identify sentiment patterns, top complaints, top praised features, and changes in customer perception.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Analyze review ratings distribution and trends over time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Extract simple sentiment signals from text data using keyword-based methods.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify recurring positive and negative themes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Correlate text sentiment with numerical ratings.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Product teams need to understand what customers love and hate. Review data is a rich source of unsolicited feedback that can guide product improvements.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Trending sentiment can detect emerging product issues before they become widespread, and highlight features worth promoting.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **3,000 reviews** with ratings (1-5), review text snippets, product categories, and dates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from collections import Counter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 3000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PRODUCTS = [\\\"Wireless Headphones\\\", \\\"Smart Watch\\\", \\\"Laptop Stand\\\", \\\"Phone Case\\\", \\\"Bluetooth Speaker\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"POSITIVE_PHRASES = [\\\"great quality\\\", \\\"love it\\\", \\\"excellent sound\\\", \\\"comfortable fit\\\", \\\"fast delivery\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                    \\\"worth the price\\\", \\\"highly recommend\\\", \\\"sturdy build\\\", \\\"easy setup\\\", \\\"good battery\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"NEGATIVE_PHRASES = [\\\"broke quickly\\\", \\\"poor quality\\\", \\\"not worth it\\\", \\\"uncomfortable\\\", \\\"terrible battery\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                    \\\"cheap material\\\", \\\"stopped working\\\", \\\"bad packaging\\\", \\\"wrong item\\\", \\\"overpriced\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"NEUTRAL_PHRASES = [\\\"it is okay\\\", \\\"average product\\\", \\\"nothing special\\\", \\\"decent for price\\\", \\\"does the job\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2024-06-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    product = rng.choice(PRODUCTS)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rating = int(rng.choice([1,2,3,4,5], p=[0.08, 0.12, 0.15, 0.30, 0.35]))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if rating >= 4:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        phrases = list(rng.choice(POSITIVE_PHRASES, size=rng.integers(1,4), replace=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif rating <= 2:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        phrases = list(rng.choice(NEGATIVE_PHRASES, size=rng.integers(1,3), replace=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        phrases = list(rng.choice(NEUTRAL_PHRASES, size=rng.integers(1,3), replace=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    review_text = \\\". \\\".join(phrases) + \\\".\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"review_id\\\": f\\\"R{i+1:05d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"date\\\": rng.choice(dates),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"product\\\": product,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"rating\\\": rating,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"review_text\\\": review_text,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.to_period(\\\"M\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Rating range: {df['rating'].min()} - {df['rating'].max()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Empty reviews: {(df['review_text'].str.strip() == '').sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We add a simple keyword-based sentiment label.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"pos_keywords = set([\\\"great\\\", \\\"love\\\", \\\"excellent\\\", \\\"recommend\\\", \\\"worth\\\", \\\"comfortable\\\", \\\"sturdy\\\", \\\"good\\\", \\\"easy\\\", \\\"fast\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"neg_keywords = set([\\\"broke\\\", \\\"poor\\\", \\\"terrible\\\", \\\"cheap\\\", \\\"stopped\\\", \\\"bad\\\", \\\"wrong\\\", \\\"overpriced\\\", \\\"uncomfortable\\\", \\\"not worth\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def simple_sentiment(text):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    words = text.lower().split()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    pos_count = sum(1 for w in words if w in pos_keywords)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    neg_count = sum(1 for w in words if w in neg_keywords)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if pos_count > neg_count:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Positive\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif neg_count > pos_count:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Negative\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return \\\"Neutral\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"sentiment\\\"] = df[\\\"review_text\\\"].apply(simple_sentiment)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(df[\\\"sentiment\\\"].value_counts())\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"rating\\\"].value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Rating Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"sentiment\\\"].value_counts().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1], color=[\\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"#e74c3c\\\", \\\"#f39c12\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Sentiment Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"product\\\")[\\\"rating\\\"].mean().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[2], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Avg Rating by Product\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Sentiment Trend Over Time\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"monthly_rating = df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"rating\\\"].mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.plot(monthly_rating.index.astype(str), monthly_rating.values, marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"steelblue\\\", linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Average Rating Over Time\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Avg Rating\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Sentiment proportion over time\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sent_monthly = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"month\\\"], df[\\\"sentiment\\\"], normalize=\\\"index\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sent_monthly.plot(kind=\\\"area\\\", stacked=True, ax=ax, color=[\\\"#e74c3c\\\", \\\"#f39c12\\\", \\\"#2ecc71\\\"], alpha=0.8)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Sentiment Proportion Over Time\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Proportion\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Top Complaint and Praise Keywords\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"neg_reviews = df[df[\\\"sentiment\\\"] == \\\"Negative\\\"][\\\"review_text\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pos_reviews = df[df[\\\"sentiment\\\"] == \\\"Positive\\\"][\\\"review_text\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Extract common phrases\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def count_phrases(texts, phrase_list):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    counts = Counter()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for text in texts:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        text_lower = text.lower()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for phrase in phrase_list:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            if phrase in text_lower:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                counts[phrase] += 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return counts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"neg_counts = count_phrases(neg_reviews, NEGATIVE_PHRASES)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pos_counts = count_phrases(pos_reviews, POSITIVE_PHRASES)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.Series(dict(pos_counts.most_common(10))).plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"#2ecc71\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Top Praised Phrases\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].invert_yaxis()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.Series(dict(neg_counts.most_common(10))).plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"#e74c3c\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Top Complaint Phrases\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].invert_yaxis()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Rating vs Sentiment Cross-Check\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"cross = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"rating\\\"], df[\\\"sentiment\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(cross, annot=True, fmt=\\\"d\\\", cmap=\\\"YlOrRd\\\", ax=ax)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Rating vs Sentiment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Sentiment and ratings align well** — high ratings correspond to positive sentiment and vice versa.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **\\\"broke quickly\\\" and \\\"poor quality\\\" are the most common negative phrases,** indicating product durability concerns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **\\\"great quality\\\" and \\\"comfortable fit\\\" are the most praised attributes.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Rating trends remain relatively stable** over the analysis period, with no major drops.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Products with lower average ratings deserve per-SKU investigation.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Keyword-based sentiment is simplistic; NLP models would be more accurate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic review text lacks the complexity of real reviews.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No verified purchase distinction.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No aspect-level sentiment extraction.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use transformer-based sentiment models (VADER, BERT) for production analysis.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Implement aspect-based sentiment to isolate specific feature feedback.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Set up automated alerts for sudden sentiment drops.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Route negative reviews to customer support for proactive follow-up.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Use positive review themes in marketing copy.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Relying only on star ratings.** Text contains richer feedback than a single number.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Not accounting for review volume.** A product with 5.0 avg from 3 reviews is unreliable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Ignoring neutral reviews.** They often contain the most constructive feedback.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Using basic keyword matching in production.** Sarcasm, negation, and context require NLP.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Not tracking sentiment trends.** A slowly declining trend is a leading indicator of product issues.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use VADER (from `nltk`) for sentiment scoring and compare to keyword-based results.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Create a word cloud for positive vs negative reviews.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Track per-product sentiment over time — which product is improving/declining?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Build a review length vs rating relationship chart.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Identify reviews where rating and sentiment disagree (e.g., 5-star with negative text).\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Review sentiment analysis provides actionable product feedback** beyond what ratings alone capture.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Quality and durability are the primary negative themes,** worth investigating in manufacturing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Tracking sentiment trends over time** is critical for early detection of issues.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Keyword-based analysis is a good starting point** but should be upgraded to NLP for production use.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
